#: src/rust-next/alternative-cargo-registries.md:1
msgid "Alternative Cargo registries"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/alternative-cargo-registries.md:3
msgid ""
"Initially added: ![Minimum Rust version: 1.34](https://img.shields.io/badge/"
"Minimum%20Rust%20Version-1.34-brightgreen.svg)"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/alternative-cargo-registries.md:5
msgid ""
"For various reasons, you may not want to publish code to crates.io, but you "
"may want to share it with others. For example, maybe your company writes "
"Rust code that's not open source, but you'd still like to use these internal "
"packages."
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/alternative-cargo-registries.md:10
msgid "Cargo supports alternative registries by settings in `.cargo/config`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/alternative-cargo-registries.md:12
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[registries]\n"
"my-registry = { index = \"https://my-intranet:7878/git/index\" }\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/alternative-cargo-registries.md:17
msgid ""
"When you want to depend on a package from another registry, you add that in "
"to your `Cargo.toml`:"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/alternative-cargo-registries.md:20
msgid ""
"```toml\n"
"[dependencies]\n"
"other-crate = { version = \"1.0\", registry = \"my-registry\" }\n"
"```"
msgstr ""

#: src/rust-next/alternative-cargo-registries.md:25
msgid ""
"To learn more, check out the [registries section of the Cargo book](https://"
"doc.rust-lang.org/nightly/cargo/reference/registries.html)."
msgstr ""
